{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam between summary persistence and findings store. MOCK-MISS: this failure appears when write-path logic and stored findings interact; a pure function test can miss repository/query wiring bugs. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no real OS/network/subprocess, no model-quality dependence, no multi-agent pipeline required. Rejection-gate: behavior text is about \"stored dimension finding\" and \"same round\" consistency, which disqualifies Unit-only happy-path but does not require System/Agentic/Workflow.","test_description":"Run an integration test with real repository wiring (e.g., local test DB). Seed round findings including at least one FAIL, attempt to store PASS summary for that round, assert write is rejected with explicit error and no PASS summary row/state is committed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam between gate evaluator, findings repository, and summary payload. MOCK-HIDE: if evaluator is tested in isolation with prebuilt objects, data-source precedence bugs (summary text trusted over store) can be hidden. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP checks are negative. Rejection-gate: behavior explicitly says \"reads per-dimension stored findings directly\" and \"does not rely only on hand-written summary text,\" indicating integration of modules, not external infra or model judgment.","test_description":"Wire gate service with real persistence adapters in test mode. Persist findings containing FAIL, pass in manual summary text claiming PASS, execute stop-gate computation, and assert verdict is FAIL/block based on stored findings rather than summary text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam across request handling, override policy, and audit-record sink. MOCK-MISS: a unit test of flag parsing alone misses failure to persist or emit the audit warning. REAL-INFRA: auditable record can be validated with local store/logger integration; no required real network/OS primitive in behavior text. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP are not required. Rejection-gate: behavior text requires both \"explicit override flag\" and \"auditable warning record,\" which disqualifies Unit-only but does not mandate System/Agentic.","test_description":"Integration test two paths: (1) manual override text without flag -> rejected; (2) same override with explicit flag -> accepted but warning/audit record is written with actor, round, reason, and timestamp fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Seam-map: multi-step orchestration seam (fix phase -> updated diff -> new review-agent round -> finalize gate). The failure is temporal/order-dependent across pipeline stages, not a single module decision. LLM-DEP on output quality is not the key, but this is still a full agent pipeline sequencing rule, so Workflow is the minimum seam level. Rejection-gate: behavior text explicitly requires \"After Phase 4 fixes\" plus \"fresh review-agent round\" before final PASS, which disqualifies isolated Integration tests that skip end-to-end orchestration state transitions.","test_description":"Execute a workflow test over the real orchestration path: create a round with failures, apply Phase 4 fixes (new diff revision), attempt finalize without rerun and assert blocked, then run a new review-agent round tied to the updated diff and assert finalize can proceed only after that fresh round exists.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.27,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.52}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam between round-limit policy, findings state, and outcome emitter. MOCK-MISS: single-function tests can miss how exhausted-round counters and unresolved findings combine at decision boundary. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP: not required by behavior text; findings can be fixture data. MULTI-STEP: state can be represented in-process without running real agent pipeline. Rejection-gate: behavior text focuses on policy decision from stored state (\"rounds are exhausted\" + \"unresolved MUST-FIX\"), so Integration is sufficient and System/Agentic/Workflow are not required.","test_description":"Integration test with wired policy service and persistence: seed maxed-out round count and unresolved MUST-FIX findings, run finalize decision, assert emitted outcome is ESCALATION (or equivalent) and PASS is not emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.1}}]}
